cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.IT, cs.SY 

This paper deals with countermeasures against fault-injection attacks on cryptographic systems, specifically CRT-RSA. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves optimization and design of countermeasures, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also involves mathematical concepts such as modular arithmetic, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
